<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1294,1514]" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">
It has long been apparent that this species was misplaced in 
<emphasis box="[879,997,1295,1320]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicName box="[879,993,1295,1320]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Scortizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Scortizus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Characters that place this species in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,316,1333,1358]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Onorelucanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,316,1333,1358]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">Onorelucanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
include the simple male genitalic capsule; convex, unarmed pronotum; and toothed mesotibiae and metatibiae in both sexes. The name 
<taxonomicName authority="Fukinuki" authorityName="Fukinuki" box="[633,868,1372,1398]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Scortizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ismaeli">
<emphasis box="[633,749,1372,1397]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">S. ismaeli</emphasis>
Fukinuki
</taxonomicName>
, represents a mandibular variant from the same locality as 
<emphasis box="[280,451,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicName box="[280,446,1411,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Scortizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulverosus">O. pulverosus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
We have examined intermediate forms, and thus the name is reduced to synonymy with 
<taxonomicName box="[213,381,1449,1474]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Scortizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulverosus">
<emphasis box="[213,381,1449,1474]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="40">O. pulverosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This situation exemplifies the undesirability of naming new species based on a single specimen and without a detailed study of the genus as a whole, or at the very least, some form of peer review.
</paragraph>
